Depth-First Traversals
Problem. Given a binary tree, visit 
every node in the tree and perform 
some operation (e.g. delete the 
node, print the node, etc.) 
Solution. Start at the root and use 
recursion to traverse the left and 
right subtrees. 
Pre-order Traversal. Perform the 
operation before traversing the left 
and right subtrees.
Post-order Traversal. Perform the 
operation after traversing the left 
and right subtrees.
void preOrder(Node<T>* node) { 
    if (node == nullptr) return; 
    do_something(); 
    preOrder(node->left); 
    preOrder(node->right); 
}
void preOrder(Node<T>* node) { 
    if (node == nullptr) return; 
    preOrder(node->left); 
    preOrder(node->right); 
    do_something(); 
}
In-order Traversal. Perform the 
operation after traversing the left 
subtree and before traversing the 
right subtree.
void inOrder(Node<T>* node) { 
    if (node == nullptr) return; 
    inOrder(node->left); 
    do_something(); 
    inOrder(node->right); 
}

